The Chinese mainland recorded 1,415 new confirmed COVID-19 cases on Tuesday, with 1,383 linked to local transmissions and 32 from overseas, according to data from the National Health Commission on Wednesday. A total of 19,199 new asymptomatic cases were also recorded on Tuesday, and 113,950 asymptomatic patients remain under medical observation. Confirmed cases on the Chinese mainland now total 158,793, with the death toll at 4,638. The latest tally of confirmed cases in the Hong Kong and Macao special administrative regions and Taiwan region is as follows: Hong Kong: 306,389 (52,793 recoveries, 8,349 deaths) Macao: 82 (82 recoveries) Taiwan: 24,866 (13,742 recoveries, 853 deaths)